Thought for 4 seconds
Here’s a refined take on “Blasphemous Rumours” by Depeche Mode:

🌀 Summary of the Lyrics
The song narrates two tragic stories:

A 16‑year‑old girl who attempts suicide out of despair yet survives—only for her mother to thank “the Lord” sarcastically for this “mercy.”

A young woman (18) who finds hope in religion, only to die suddenly in a car accident on a bright summer’s day.

The haunting refrain goes:

“I don’t want to start any blasphemous rumours,
But I think that God’s got a sick sense of humour—
And when I die, I expect to find Him laughing.”

It wrestles with the tension between faith and suffering, asking:
If God is all-powerful and loving, why does tragedy strike the innocent?

📚 Song Background & Reactions
Written by Martin Gore, inspired by early church experiences and the “prayer list” wherein praying for the sick—with many still dying—felt deeply hypocritical 
Wikipedia
